A poem for my brother. Reflecting on life, family, and the passage of time. In Remembrance Memorial and Remembrance for Ranjiv
Too Young to Die Once I was four years old, i told my mama &ldquo;Pretty woman walking down the streah haha&rdquo; Then she shouted at me and i said mama &ldquo;You ugly woman, yacking down the stream yah&rdquo;
That was then and the world was smaller And everything was so simpler and life was gentler My brother and I were running down the roads in Sodnac Drinking our dad&rsquo;s secret stash of cognac
